TITLE: Incorrect Usage of Cancellation Token in Resilience Pipeline with Timeout
DESCRIPTION: This example shows the incorrect pattern where the callback ignores the innerToken passed from the pipeline and instead uses outerToken. This prevents the timeout strategy from properly cancelling the operation after the specified timeout period.
SOURCE: https://github.com/app-vnext/polly/blob/main/docs/strategies/timeout.md#2025-04-18_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var pipeline = new ResiliencePipelineBuilder()
    .AddTimeout(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(1))
    .Build();

await pipeline.ExecuteAsync(
    async innerToken => await Task.Delay(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(3), outerToken), // The delay call should use innerToken
    outerToken);
```

