TITLE: Visualizing Happy Path Retry Sequence with Mermaid
DESCRIPTION: A sequence diagram illustrating the happy path flow of a retry strategy with a maximum of 2 retry attempts. It shows the interaction between the caller, pipeline, retry strategy, and the decorated user callback, resulting in a successful execution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/app-vnext/polly/blob/main/docs/strategies/retry.md#2025-04-18_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: mermaid
CODE:
```
sequenceDiagram
    actor C as Caller
    participant P as Pipeline
    participant R as Retry
    participant D as DecoratedUserCallback

    C->>P: Calls ExecuteAsync
    P->>R: Calls ExecuteCore
    Note over R,D: Initial attempt
    R->>+D: Invokes
    D->>-R: Fails
    R-->>R: Sleeps
    Note over R,D: 1st retry attempt
    R->>+D: Invokes
    D->>-R: Returns result
    R->>P: Returns result
    P->>C: Returns result
```

